<TITLE> Police link death of Jatrabari resident to poverty </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 19 (bdnews24.com) A man was found dead at his Jatrabari home in Dhaka Tuesday night, and the police linked the circumstances surrounding his death to poverty. Jatrabari police sub-inspector Abdur Razzak told bdnews24.com Wednesday that 28-year-old Jibon Rahman Imon had been found hanging from an electric fan off the ceiling of his house by wife Kamala Begum. Police believe Imon committed suicide. Imon asked Kamala for some food when he returned home Tuesday night, but his wife said she had not enough rice to cook for the family, the police officer said. Kamala then went out to buy some rice from a shop as she was asked to do so by her husband, Razzak said. Kamala came back home only to see her husband dead, the police officer said. Police believe Imon committed suicide. The body was sent to Mitford Hospital for an autopsy. bdn
